name: 2x2 Megaminx
description: A smaller feat than the traditional Megaminx, but make no mistake, you can easily get lost in it!

name: Zetaminx (13x13 Megaminx)
description: At nine orders of magnitude larger than the original Megaminx, this puzzle has 2,532 stickers.

name: Windmill Cube
description: A variation on the Axis Cube in which instead of moving the pieces to a corner, we simply rotate the edges on one axis, causing corners to become edges, and edges to become corners while leaving the centers untouched.

name: 11x11 Cube
description: This cube is so large that its predecessor (the 10x10 cube) can't even be built because it lacks the necessary structure found in odd-numbered cubes. It has 726 stickers! Good luck!

name: 6x6 Cube
description: At three orders of magnitude larger than the original Rubik's Cube, this cube has 216 stickers.

name: 7x7 Cube
description: At four orders of magnitude larger than the original Rubik's Cube, this cube has 294 stickers.

name: 5x5 Cube
description: At two orders of magnitude larger than the original Rubik's Cube, this cube has 150 stickers.

name: 9x9 Cube
description: At a whopping six orders of magnitude larger than the original Rubik's Cube, this cube has 486 stickers.

name: Original Megaminx (3x3 Megaminx)
description: The traditional Megaminx. Its a dodecahedron shaped puzzle with 50 moving pieces. It shares a lot of similarities with the original Rubik's cube, but also contains mysteries of its own.

name: Teraminx (7x7 Megaminx)
description: At four orders of magnitude larger than the original Megaminx, this puzzle has 732 stickers.

name: Gigaminx (5x5 Megaminx)
description: At two orders of magnitude larger than the original Megaminx, this puzzle has 372 stickers.

name: Petaminx (9x9 Megaminx)
description: At five orders of magnitude larger than the original Megaminx, this puzzle has 1,212 stickers.

name: Rubik's Cube (3x3 Cube)
description: The traditional twisty puzzle from the '80s. Twist it and watch as the colors get increasingly mixed up then test your skill at unscrambling it.

name: Yottaminx (15x15 Megaminx)
description: At an incredible eleven orders of magnitude larger than the original Megaminx, this puzzle has startling 3,372 stickers. You're gonna need a day or two for this one

name: Kilominx (4x4 Megaminx)
description: This puzzle compares to the original Megaminx is equivalent to the comparison between a 4x4 Cube and an original Rubik's cube.

name: Skewb
description: A classic favorite. The Skewb slides along an axis underneath each of its corners, causing the corners to shuffle while leaving the centers mostly in place.

name: Master Skewb
description: Considered to be the next level above the Skewb, this puzzle adds the new challenge of not only fixing the corners, but now the centers as well.

name: Square-1
description: A puzzle which punishes you for not paying attention. You can only twist it if the correct pieces line up with the only slice down the cube. This can lead to some interesting combinations.

name: Square-2
description: The next level after the Square-1, this cube adds extra pieces to make lining them up even harder.

name: Axis Cube
description: This cube works by taking an original Rubik's cube, and pushing all the pieces out of whack. The centers become corners, the corners become edges, and the edges become centers.

name: Fisher Cube
description: When you turn this puzzle, you will quickly find that it loses its familiar cube-like shape! Branded as a shape-shifter, this puzzle will confuse anyone!

name: Helicopter Cube
description: Twisting the edges causes the pieces to swag in a "helicopter blade" style, hence the name.

name: Siamese Cube
description: Two Rubik's cubes fused together along on corner, this will be a challenge to unscramble!

name: 2x2 Pyraminx
description: While this puzzle is possible to "scramble", you will find that there are only three moving parts and should be able to solve it very easilly! Still a great addition for collectors!

name: 1x1 Cube
description: The smallest and most trivial of the cubic puzzles. Comes pre-solved!

name: 5x5 Pyraminx
description: The largest pyramidal puzzle in existence today, this puzzle requires serious discipline to master. Notice the curved shape, it must be designed that way to accommodate all the pieces!

name: 4x4 Pyraminx
description: The next higher order puzzle from the traditional Pyraminx. Good luck with this one.

name: Original Pyraminx (3x3 Pyraminx)
description: The traditional Pyraminx puzzle. It turns on its 4 exes stemming inwards from each tip of the puzzle. Watch as the pieces get quickly mixed up and try to put them back!

name: 1x1 Pyraminx
description: The smallest and most trivial of the pyramidal puzzles. Comes pre-solved!

name: 2x2 Cube
description: Some mistake this as an easy puzzle since it's smaller than the traditional Rubik's cube. While they are correct that it has less pieces, they will find themselves lost if they try to unscramble it!

name: Monominx (1x1 Megaminx)
description: The smallest and most trivial of the dodecahedral puzzles. Comes pre-solved!

name: 8x8 Cube
description: At five orders of magnitude larger than the original Rubik's Cube, this cube has 384 stickers.

name: 4x4 Cube
description: 54 stickers not enough for you? Try out this next level puzzle with 96 stickers!
